<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7AFFDCFCE29345FA4FF881" blockId="8.[816,1459,1808,1833]" box="[816,1459,1808,1833]" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
<heading id="D0A94D3DCD7AFFDCFCE29345FA4FF881" box="[816,1459,1808,1833]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7AFFDCFCE29345FA4FF881" bold="true" box="[816,1459,1808,1833]" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7AFFDCFBDF9344FB72F881" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1912" box="[1037,1166,1808,1832]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7AFFDCFBDF9344FB72F881" bold="true" box="[1037,1166,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">Microglanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the rio Amazon basin
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344A9DACD7AFFDDFCE29305FCFFFB43" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="706" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" type="key">
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7AFFDDFCE29305FCFFFEA3" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="706" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7AFFDCFCE29305FA4FF800" blockId="8.[816,1459,1873,1961]" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7AFFDCFCE29305FA4FF800" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">1. Absence of light transverse band on nape; presence of melanophores surrounding the neuromasts of superficial lines, forming series of black dots ....................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF5394E6FCFFFEA3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF5394E6FCFFFEA3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">1’. Presence of a light transverse band on nape; absence of melanophores surrounding the neuromasts of superficial lines .......................................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF539546FCF8FE63" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539546FCFFFEC3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539546FCFFFEC3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
2. Dark brown trunk with light brown stripes imparting a ground color similar to tree bark; absence of light marks on nape; snout length 11.4-12.9% SL ........ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFE209506FCFFFEC3" box="[498,771,338,362]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xylographicus">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFE209506FCFFFEC3" box="[498,771,338,362]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Microglanis xylographicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539526FCF8FE63" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539526FCF8FE63" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
2’. Light brown trunk with dark brown saddles below dorsal and adipose fins; light cordiform blotch on nape; snout length 9.1-10.7% SL .............................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDFE95E6FCF8FE63" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Shibatta" authorityYear="2010" box="[556,772,434,458]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFDFE95E6FCF8FE63" box="[556,772,434,458]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Microglanis robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF539586FCFFFD83" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539586FCFFFDA3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539586FCFFFDA3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
3. Very wide dark-brown stripes on fins ................... 
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFF4D95A7FCFFFDA3" box="[159,771,498,522]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
...................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFE2295A6FCFFFDA3" authorityName="Mees" authorityYear="1978" box="[496,771,498,522]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pellopterygius">Microglanis pellopterygius</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539646FCFFFD83" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" box="[129,771,530,554]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539646FCFFFD83" box="[129,771,530,554]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">3’. Dark brown stripes on fins absent or narrow ..................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF539666FCFFFD63" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539666FCFFFD23" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539666FCFFFD23" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
4. Lateral line long, reaching the vertical line through middle of adipose fin; number of pores 14-20 ........................ 
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFF4D9627FCFFFD23" box="[159,771,626,650]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDE49626FCFFFD23" authorityName="Gomes" authorityYear="1946" box="[566,771,626,650]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iheringi">Microglanis iheringi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF5396C6FCFFFD63" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF5396C6FCFFFD63" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">4’. Lateral line short, not reaching the vertical line through middle of adipose fin; number of pores 3-9 ......................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF539686FCFFFC83" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539686FCFFFCA3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539686FCFFFCA3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
5. Tip of pectoral-fin spine bifurcated ...................... 
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFF4D96A7FCFFFCA3" box="[159,771,754,778]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
............................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDF696A6FCFFFCA3" authorityName="Mees" authorityYear="1974" box="[548,771,754,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="secundus">Microglanis secundus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539746FCFFFC83" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" box="[129,771,786,810]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539746FCFFFC83" box="[129,771,786,810]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">5’. Tip of pectoral-fin spine undivided ................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF539766FCFFFC43" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539766FCFFFCC3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539766FCFFFCC3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
6. Caudal fin rounded; all anterior serrae of the pectoral spine retrorse, except the last antrorse ........... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDE39706FCFFFCC3" authorityName="Eigenmann &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1942" box="[561,771,850,874]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zonatus">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFDE39706FCFFFCC3" box="[561,771,850,874]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Microglanis zonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539726FCFFFC43" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539726FCFFFC43" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">6’. Caudal fin slightly bilobed; upper lobe of caudal fin more developed than lower lobe; anterior serrae of pectoral-fin spine antrorse and retrorse, with a single Y-shaped serration in between ............................................................ 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AAE2F4CD7BFFDDFF5397A7FCFFFB43" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF5397A7FCFFFBC3" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF5397A7FCFFFBC3" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
7. Lateral line reaching the vertical through middle of dorsalfin base; 5-7 total gill rakers in the first branchial arch; 6 pleural ribs; i,12,i caudal-fin rays ........................... ................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDFD9006FCFFFBC3" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1912" box="[559,771,1106,1130]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poecilus">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFDFD9006FCFFFBC3" box="[559,771,1106,1130]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Microglanis poecilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1FA51CD7BFFDDFF539026FCFFFB43" blockId="9.[129,772,178,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
<keyLead id="30AF5964CD7BFFDDFF539026FCFFFB43" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">
7’. Lateral line reaching the vertical through base of dorsalfin spine; 3-6 total gill rakers in the first branchial arch; 4-5 pleural ribs; i,10,i or i,11,i caudal-fin rays ..................... ................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E81D2CD7BFFDDFDFF9086FCFFFB43" box="[557,771,1234,1258]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pseudopimelodidae" genus="Microglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oliveirai">
<emphasis id="B92A2643CD7BFFDDFDFF9086FCFFFB43" box="[557,771,1234,1258]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="706">Microglanis oliveirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
